Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of two main parts: a larger castle-like structure and a separate smaller arch
- There are approximately 3 layers in the main structure
- Colors used include orange (triangular roof pieces), red (arch pieces), blue (cube), green (cube), and yellow (cubes)
- The structure has a symmetrical design with an arch in the middle
- Total number of blocks used: approximately 12-13 blocks

Block Selection and Assembly Order:
The structure can be built from bottom up, starting with the main structure and then the separate arch.

Assembly Instructions:
{
Step1: Move block with index 9 (yellow cube, left base)
Step2: Move block with index 9 (yellow cube, right base)
Step3: Move block with index 2 (red arch center)
Step4: Move block with index 7 (blue cube, upper level)
Step5: Move block with index 8 (green cube, upper level)
Step6: Move block with index 13 (orange triangle, left roof)
Step7: Move block with index 14 (orange triangle, center roof)
Step8: Move block with index 15 (orange triangle, right slope)
Step9: Move block with index 16 (orange triangle, far right slope)
Step10: Move block with index 10 (orange vertical piece, left side)
Step11: Move block with index 11 (orange vertical piece, right side)
Step12: Move block with index 1 (red arch piece, separate structure)
}

This assembly sequence should recreate the target structure exactly as shown in the main image, using the blocks from the dictionary in their exact orientations without any rotation.
